definitions.definition: Not reaching orbit ; having a trajectory that does not reach orbital velocity and so must return to ground eventually.
examples: The first rocket test was suborbital ; it didn't even get off the ground but rather exploded on the launchpad.

definitions.definition: Below the orbit of the eye .
